         <div type="entry">
                <head>Ishoʿyahb IV</head>
                <ab type="idnos">
                    <idno type="URI">https://gedsh.bethmardutho.org/Ishoyahb-IV</idno>
                    <idno type="syriaca-bibl">http://syriaca.org/bibl/299</idno>
                    <idno type="entry">290</idno>
                    <milestone unit="pages" n="219"/>
                    <idno type="subject">http://syriaca.org/person/562</idno>
                    <note type="type">person</note>
                    <note type="abstract">
                        <abbr>Cath.</abbr> (1021-5) and <abbr>bp.</abbr> of Beth Nuhadra; 
                        exegete of the <orgName>School of Mar
                        Mari</orgName>.<note/>
                    </note>
                </ab>
                <ab type="infobox">(d. 1025) [Ch. of E.]</ab>
                <div type="body">
                    <p>
                        <abbr>Cath.</abbr> (1021–5) and formerly <abbr>bp.</abbr> of <ref rend="bold" target="https://gedsh.bethmardutho.org/Beth-Nuhadra">
                            <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/36">Beth Nuhadra</placeName>
                        </ref>,
                        and exegete of the School of Mar Mari. His election was disputed and a
                        letter by <ref rend="bold" target="https://gedsh.bethmardutho.org/Eliya-of-Nisibis">
                            <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/472">Eliya of
                            Nisibis</persName>
                        </ref> on the subject survives (<abbr>ed.</abbr> B. Vandenhoff, in <title rend="italic">
                            <abbr>OC</abbr>
                        </title> 11 [1913]). Ishoʿyahb has been identified (by van
                        Unnik) as the author of a series of 123 Questions and Answers on the
                        Eucharist attributed in the <abbr>mss.</abbr> to <ref rend="bold"
                       target="https://gedsh.bethmardutho.org/Ishoyahb-III-of-Adiabene">
                            <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/561">Ishoʿyahb</persName>
                        </ref> the
                        Great (<choice>
                            <sic>i.e. </sic>
                            <corr>i.e., </corr>
                        </choice>III). Neither  <ref rend="bold" target="https://gedsh.bethmardutho.org/Abdisho-bar-Brikha">
                            <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/310">ʿAbdishoʿ</persName>
                        </ref> in his
                        ‘Catalogue’, nor any other ancient source, attributes any works to Ishoʿyahb
                        IV.</p>
                </div>
                <div type="bibl">
                    <listBibl>
                        <listBibl>
                            <head>Primary Sources</head>
                            <bibl>J.  Isaac, ‘Questions sur le Baptême par Ishoʿyahb IV’, <title rend="italic">Bayn al-Nahrayn</title> 80 (20) (1992), 52–87.
                                (photographic edition with <abbr>AT</abbr>)</bibl>
                            <bibl>W. C.  van Unnik, <title rend="italic">Nestorian Questions on the
                                    Administration of the Eucharist, by Ishoʿyabh IV</title> (1937;
                                <abbr>repr.</abbr> 1970).</bibl>
                        </listBibl>
                        <listBibl>
                            <head>Secondary Sources</head>
